# Java Setup Guide for Windows

This guide explains how to set up Java development on a Windows system step by step.

---

## Step 1: Install Java JDK

1. Visit the official website:
   https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/downloads/

2. Download the latest Java Development Kit (JDK)

3. Run the installer and complete the installation process

---

## Step 2: Set Environment Variables

### Set JAVA_HOME

1. Open Start Menu and search for "Environment Variables"
2. Click "Edit the system environment variables"
3. Click "Environment Variables"
4. Under System Variables, click "New"

   * Variable Name: JAVA_HOME
   * Variable Value:
     C:\Program Files\Java\jdk-XX

---

### Update PATH

1. In System Variables, select "Path" and click "Edit"
2. Click "New" and add:
   %JAVA_HOME%\bin

---

## Step 3: Verify Installation

Open Command Prompt and run:

```bash
java -version
javac -version
```

If Java is installed correctly, the version details will be displayed.

---

## Step 4: Install IDE

Recommended options:

* IntelliJ IDEA
* Visual Studio Code

---

## Step 5: Install Git

1. Download Git from: https://git-scm.com/
2. Install using default settings
3. Verify installation:

```bash
git --version
```

---

## Step 6: First Java Program

Create a file named HelloWorld.java

```java
public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello, Java!");
    }
}
```

---

## Step 7: Compile and Run

```bash
javac HelloWorld.java
java HelloWorld
```

---

## Common Issues

* JAVA_HOME is not set correctly
* Incorrect JDK installation path
* PATH variable not updated
* Installed JRE instead of JDK

---

## Conclusion

Java is now successfully installed and ready for development on your Windows system.
